properties.headline: Lake Wind Advisory issued January 13 at 1:29PM PST until January 13 at 7:00PM PST by NWS Reno NV
properties.description:
* CHANGES...None.

* WHAT...For the Lake Wind Advisory in effect today, southwest
winds 15 to 20 mph with gusts up to 35 mph. Waves 2 to 4 feet.
For the Lake Wind Advisory in effect Tuesday, southwest winds
15 to 25 mph with gusts up to 40 mph expected. Waves 2 to 4
feet.

* WHERE...Lake Tahoe.

* WHEN...For the first Lake Wind Advisory, until 7 PM PST this
evening. For the second Lake Wind Advisory, from 10 AM to 7 PM
PST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Small boats, kayaks and paddle boards will be prone
to capsizing and should remain off lake waters until
conditions improve.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Winds will become stronger after 7 PM PST
this evening resulting in worse lake conditions...this is
covered in the Winter Weather Advisory.
properties.instruction:
Check lake conditions before heading out and be prepared for a
sudden increase in winds and wave heights. Consider postponing
boating activities on the lake until a day with less wind.
